    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Bis-HEMA Poly(Diglycol Adipate)/IPDI Copolymer is a urethane polymer formed by a multi-step process. First, a polyester is made by condensing Diethylene Glycol and Adipic Acid, which is subsequently reacted with Isophorone Diisocyanate. The resulting polymer is end-capped with HEMA."
